    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-03-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="45"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                <head>45. National Security Action Memorandum No. 291<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d45fn1">Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_SS1"
                            >S/S</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files: Lot 72 D 316,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss> 291. Secret. Copies were sent to
                            <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss> Administrator <persName
                            corresp="#p_BDE1">David E. Bell</persName> and Director of Central
                        Intelligence <persName corresp="#p_MCJA1">John A. McCone</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-03-20">March 20, 1964</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>MEMORANDUM FOR</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President is quite concerned over the prospect that we may very quickly lose
                    our base rights in Libya. While fully recognizing that events may be moving so
                    fast that we will be unable to hold on for much longer, he desires that we make
                    every reasonable effort to prolong our stay, consistent with our longer-term
                    objective of preserving the independence and stability of Libya.</p>
                <p>He asks that the Department of State, in conjunction with other interested
                    agencies, prepare an action program to this end, which he would like to review
                    by 10 April.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">McGeorge Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
